// Figure 4.7: Routing Delegation Strategy
// Host selects remote → Remote handles internal routes → Navigation sync

// ==================== ACTORS ====================
Browser [icon: chrome, color: blue]
Host Router [icon: git-branch, color: green]
Registry [icon: list, color: orange]
Store Remote [icon: shopping-bag, color: cyan]
Checkout Remote [icon: shopping-cart, color: purple]
Account Remote [icon: user, color: pink]

// ==================== ROUTE RESOLUTION ====================
Browser > Host Router : URL: /store/product/123
Host Router > Registry : Match basePath '/store'
Registry > Host Router : Store config
Host Router > Store Remote : Load + inject
Store Remote > Host Router : Handle /product/123 internally

// ==================== PROTECTED ROUTES ====================
Browser > Host Router : URL: /checkout/cart
Host Router > Registry : Match basePath '/checkout'
Host Router > Host Router : Check auth (ProtectedRoute)
Host Router > Checkout Remote : Load if authenticated

// ==================== NAVIGATION SYNC ====================
Store Remote > Host Router : onNavigate('/store/product/456')
Host Router > Browser : Update browser history

// ==================== ROUTE OWNERSHIP ====================
// Host owns: route prefix matching, auth guards, history
// Remote owns: internal subroutes, feature logic
